SEC. 2. The members of the Commission shall be appointed by the President of the Philippines with the consent of the Commission on Appointments and shall be composed of the following;

Twenty shall be designated by the President of the Philippines upon the recommendation of organizations interested in educational, scientific and cultural matters affiliated with and duly registered in the Commission;

Eight shall represent educational, scientific, and cultural agencies of the Government; and,

Two shall be designated at the discretion of the President.

A Chairman and Vice-Chairman shall be elected by the Commission to serve for a term of one year or until their respective successors shall have been elected or qualified. The Chairman shall be the presiding officer of the Commission and shall ex-officio be the Head of the Executive Committee herein provided.

SEC. 6. The Commission shall have the following powers and duties:

To meet at least once a year on such date and place as it might designate;

With the approval of the Secretary of Foreign Affairs, to promulgate rules and regulations for the conduct of its own affairs;

To advise the Government of the Philippines on matters relating to the UNESCO and on the best ways and means by which educational, scientific, and cultural developments could be best taken advantage of by the Philippines;

To advise Philippine delegations to the UNESCO Conference;

To serve as a liaison agency between the Government of the Philippines and the UNESCO;

To associate the principal bodies in the Philippines actually interested in educational, scientific, and cultural matters with the work of the UNESCO; and

To submit an annual report to the President and the Congress of its activities and accomplishments during the year.

SEC. 7. There is hereby authorized to be appropriated the amount of one hundred and twenty thousand pesos or so much thereof as may be necessary for the immediate organization and operation of the Commission up to and including the fiscal year 1951-1952.
